:false},{"lineNumber":10,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"## Overview: B2B4U","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":11,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":12,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"B2B4U is a desktop contact management application made for business consultants, optimized for use via a Command Line Interface (CLI) while still having the benefits of a Graphical User Interface (GUI).","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":13,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"If you can type fast, B2B4U can get your human resource management tasks done faster than traditional GUI apps.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":14,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":15,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"Given below are my contributions to the project.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":16,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":17,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"## New Features","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":18,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"- Added the ability to find contacts by fields","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":19,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Function: Allow users to combine field-specific keywords (e.g. name, email, address, last contacted, tags) to quickly narrow down matching contacts.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":20,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Justification: This helps consultants retrieve contacts even when they only remember partial information such as an email fragment or location keyword.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":21,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Highlights: The feature extends the existing find flow by composing predicates across multiple fields while preserving intuitive CLI usage and command feedback.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":22,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Non-trivial pull-requests: [#74](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/74), [#77](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/77), [#88](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/88)","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":23,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":24,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"## Enhancements to existing features","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":25,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"- Added a `Last Updated` field with sorting support","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":26,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Function: Track when each contact profile was most recently modified, display it in the UI, and allow sorting by this field.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":27,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Justification: Users with large contact lists can identify stale profiles and prioritise records that likely need refresh.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":28,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Highlights: Introduced model, storage, parser, UI, and comparator updates so `lastUpdated` is persisted and can be used consistently in sort and display.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":29,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Non-trivial pull-requests: [#113](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/113), [#116](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/116)","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":30,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"- Added a `Last Contacted` field","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":31,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Function: Store the latest known contact point (including flexible user input formats) for each profile.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":32,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Justification: This supports follow-up planning by making cold contacts easy to identify.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":33,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Highlights: Implemented end-to-end support from parsing and validation to model/storage integration and display.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":34,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Non-trivial pull-requests: [#109](https://github.com/AY2526S2-CS2103T-T08-1/tp/pull/109)","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":35,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"- Updated default sort","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":36,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Function: Updated the default ordering used in list/load/reset views so high-priority contacts (recently contacted/updated and urgent reminders) surface earlier.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":37,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Justification: Instead of adding a separate dashboard, this gives users an immediate overview in their primary contact list with no extra navigation.","lastModifiedDate":"2026-04-09T23:41:19","isFullCredit":false},{"lineNumber":38,"author":{"gitId":"-"},"content":"  - Highlights: Centralised default comparator logic in the model so command-driven sorts, resets, and persisted state transitions remai